Reporting-guideline flow diagrams (CONSORT, PRISMA 2020, STROBE, STARD 2015)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
The node skeletons / layouts and the count-derivation + cascade-reconciliation
logic in `src/scidraw_agent/reporting/` are reimplemented from the
**make-figures** skill by Aperivue (https://aperivue.com), licensed MIT
(Copyright (c) 2026 Aperivue). Source:

    https://github.com/Aperivue/medsci-skills  (skills/make-figures)

Specifically:
  * `reporting/templates.py` — the four flow node-skeletons translate the
    structure of make-figures'
    `references/exemplar_diagrams/{strobe,consort,prisma,stard}/template_input.yaml`
    into scidraw-agent's FigureSchema IR. Only the flow STRUCTURE (which boxes,
    spine order, where exclusion side-boxes branch) is reused — a fact/layout,
    not copyrighted checklist text.
  * `reporting/counts.py` — the count-extraction + caption-vs-flow reconciliation
    is a Python port of make-figures' `scripts/derive_figure_legend_counts.py`,
    and the placeholder count-fill of `scripts/fill_prisma_template.py`.
  * `standards/linter.py` — the numeric thresholds MIN_READABLE_PX (14px) and
    OUT_OF_PALETTE_TOLERANCE (0.15) are adopted as values from make-figures'
    `scripts/critic_figure.py`; applied structurally on the SVG (no OCR / raster
    critic is imported).

The underlying reporting guidelines remain the work of their respective
authorities (CONSORT Group, PRISMA, STROBE, STARD). No restrictive checklist
documents (e.g. CONSORT-2010 CC-BY-NC, SPIRIT CC-BY-NC-ND) are bundled; only the
flow node-skeleton/layout (an uncopyrightable fact) is reimplemented.
